Wilib/login.html.title: login
Wilib/login.html.body:
login(username, password)
From your username and password, return a client object for controlling your login
Parameters
Required:

username:String. Insert your username

password:String. Insert your password


Optional:
None
Returns:

A Client object for this login session

Example
import wilibs.wilib
client = wilib.login('username', 'password')
project.getProjectById(56)

Client/wiSavefig.html.title: wiSavefig
Client/wiSavefig.html.body:
wiSavefig(plt, fileName, **dict)
Save fig of mat plotlib
Parameters
Required:

plt:matplotlib.pyplot object

fileName:File name


Optional:

dict.*:Option for pyplot

Returns:

True

Example
import matplotlib
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
client = wilib.login('YOUR_TOKEN')
curve = client.getCurveByName(55)
dataX = []
dataY = []
for row in curve.getCurveData():
    dataX.append(row['x'])
    dataY.append(row['y'])
plt.plot(dataX, dataY)
plt.ylabel('Depth')
client.wiSavefig(plt, 'demo.png')
